
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `grep-aptavail` baraye jostojo (search) dar list-e package-haye dastres (available) dar system-e apt estefade mishavad. Shoma mitavanid be donbale esm-e package-ha ya tozihat-e anha begardid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `grep-aptavail NAME` --> 🎯 Jostojo baraye package-haye ba esm-e `NAME`.
    🔹 `grep-aptavail -s TEXT` --> 🔎 Jostojo dar tozihat (description) package-ha baraye `TEXT`.
    🔹 `grep-aptavail -x NAME` --> 💯 Jostojuye motabegh-e kamel (exact match) esm-e `NAME`.
    🔹 `grep-aptavail -v TEXT` --> 🚫 Namayesh package-hayee ke `TEXT` ra dar esm ya tozihat nadarand.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ grep-aptavail firefox

    🔹 Namayesh hame package-hayee ke "firefox" dar esm-e anha vojood darad.

    $ grep-aptavail -s "web browser"

    🔹 Namayesh hame package-hayee ke tozihat-e anha shamel "web browser" mishavad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ grep-aptavail -x "nano"

    🔹 Faghat package-hayee ra namayesh midahad ke esm-e anha دقیقاً "nano" bashad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `grep-aptavail` command is used to search the list of available packages in the apt system. You can search for package names or descriptions.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `grep-aptavail NAME` --> 🎯 Search for packages with the name `NAME`.
    🔹 `grep-aptavail -s TEXT` --> 🔎 Search package descriptions for `TEXT`.
    🔹 `grep-aptavail -x NAME` --> 💯 Search for an exact match of the name `NAME`.
    🔹 `grep-aptavail -v TEXT` --> 🚫 Show packages that do NOT contain `TEXT` in their name or description.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ grep-aptavail firefox

    🔹 Shows all packages that have "firefox" in their name.

    $ grep-aptavail -s "web browser"

    🔹 Shows all packages whose descriptions include "web browser".

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ grep-aptavail -x "nano"

    🔹 Only displays packages that have the exact name "nano".
